a million times.


907
00:51:31.480 --> 00:51:33.471
These New York types
like to come late.


908
00:51:33.691 --> 00:51:38.105
Believe me,
I've never seen one of them come on time in all my years in the theater.


909
00:51:38.320 --> 00:51:39.605
- Take a deep breath.
- Good.


910
00:51:40.239 --> 00:51:42.070
Blow it out.
He's gonna be here.


911
00:51:42.282 --> 00:51:45.945
Let's just do a good show.
Everybody do a good show.


912
00:51:46.161 --> 00:51:47.025
Hands in the middle.

913
00:52:22.448 --> 00:52:24.063
Oh, howdy!

914
00:52:25.367 --> 00:52:29.076
I didn't see you
sneak up on me there.


915
00:52:29.663 --> 00:52:33.622
But if you'd like,
you're welcome to share my campfire with me.


916
00:52:33.834 --> 00:52:36.246
I was just fixin'
to get me some grub.


917
00:52:37.254 --> 00:52:38.369
Beans.

918
00:52:40.340 --> 00:52:41.625
I love beans.

919
00:52:42.092 --> 00:52:44.504
Big, fat, hot, juicy beans.

920
00:52:44.887 --> 00:52:47.253
Now don't get me goin'
on beans,


921
00:52:47.514 --> 00:52:50.551
Or I'll be jabberin' away
'til the sun comes up.


922
00:52:51.393 --> 00:52:54.180
But, you know,
now that I've got your ear,


923
00:52:54.396 --> 00:52:57.058
There is a story I wouldn't mind
sharin' with ya.


924
00:52:57.649 --> 00:53:02.188
It's a tall tale that
grows taller with each passing year.

925
00:53:02.404 --> 00:53:05.396
It's the story of Blaine.

926
00:53:20.756 --> 00:53:22.496
Well, we've traveled
long and far today.


927
00:53:22.716 --> 00:53:24.331
We must let the women
and children rest.


928
00:53:24.551 --> 00:53:27.384
Don't you rest on our account,
Daniel Potter.


929
00:53:27.596 --> 00:53:32.135
We women are just as strong
and resilient as you men.


930
00:53:32.351 --> 00:53:35.343
I do believe ya are, Rebecca.
I do believe ya are.


931
00:53:35.604 --> 00:53:38.971
California will be a sight
for these weary eyes.


932
00:53:39.191 --> 00:53:41.352
Mine as well, Rebecca,
mine as well.


933
00:53:41.568 --> 00:53:44.025
But right now,
we need a campfire to warm our souls...


934
00:53:44.238 --> 00:53:46.695
- And to cook our food.
- Done.


935
00:53:53.121 --> 00:53:57.160
- That will be quite enough of that, Billy Whitaker.
- Just one kiss.


936
00:53:57.376 --> 00:54:00.868
There will be plenty of time
for kissin' when we get to California.

937
00:54:01.588 --> 00:54:03.544
If we get
to California.


938
00:54:03.757 --> 00:54:05.167
Oh, we'll get there.

939
00:54:05.759 --> 00:54:08.296
Blaine Fabin
will lead us there.


940
00:54:08.554 --> 00:54:10.636
Hark, a rider approaches.

941
00:54:10.848 --> 00:54:12.634
Blaine Fabin
returns.


942
00:54:13.642 --> 00:54:17.726
Whoa! Hello there.

943
00:54:18.146 --> 00:54:20.432
Whoa! Steady.

944
00:54:22.276 --> 00:54:24.483
Gather 'round,
for I have news.


945
00:54:25.195 --> 00:54:28.858
What news?
